> A mechanic I trust with all my VW parts here in Seattle, Jerry at North
West
> Connecting Rod, had some interesting things to say about the dozen or so
> aluminum blocks he has worked with. One of the things is clearance for
welded
> CW cranks. There are a lot of low budget CW cranks out there and many of
them
> need to have the case clearance. The lifter bore tops need to be surfaced
and
> chamfered to drop the lifters down enough to clear for even mild cams.
Then
> the issue of cooling because magnesium disperses heat faster than
aluminum, it
> seems to hold on to the heat raising the oil temp.
>
> Knowing all this, I decided to give one a try and have it punched out to
90.5
> and drilled for full flow.  I'm going to cork it first and try it with a
dog
> house cooler.\, but if it seems too hot I will go to an external cooler
and
> filter. Hopefully this won't end up to be the nightmare met with by
others.
